Serves 4 but just adjust chicken quantity to suit
Need to marinade 12 hours (or up to 24 hours) ahead of cooking
/////
Marinate:
    Mix the following:
          A bunch of fresh oregano, roughly chopped
          10* cloves of garlic, crushed
          10* dried dates, halved
          Half a cup pitted green olives (more if you like)
          Half a cup capers and some of their brine
          About 100 ml olive oil
          About 100 ml red wine vinegar
    Pour the above over:
          8-12 chicken thighs (bone in, skin on)
    Leave to marinade for 12+ hours, stirring once or twice
/////
Potato:
    Slice:
          4-6 potatoes into thin (<0.5cm) rings
    Lightly grease an oven tray with oil or butter
    Arrange slices of potato, overlapping, on tray
/////
Cooking:
    Pre-heat oven to 180Â°C
    Arrange chicken pieces and all the chunky marinade on top of potato
    Mix together:
          100 ml white wine
          50 ml pommegranate molasses
        Pour over tray
    Bake for 1 hour, basting with the juices every 15 minutes or so
